  "What is a statement in logic?": "",
  "Key Concepts — Logic ⭐ Statements and Truth Values A statement (or proposition) is a sentence that is either true (T) or false (F) , but not both. The other options — 'Any sentence in English', 'A question about math', and 'An unproven conjecture' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
  "What is the negation of a true statement?": "",
  "Negation (~p or ¬p) reverses the truth value: if p is true, ~p is false, and vice versa. Negation simply adds 'not' to the statement. The answer is 'False'. The other options — 'True', 'Unknown', and 'Undefined' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": "",
  "If p is 'It is raining' and p is true, what is ~p?": "",
  "Negation (~p or ¬p) reverses the truth value: if p is true, ~p is false, and vice versa. Negation simply adds 'not' to the statement. The answer is ''It is not raining' and it is false'. The other options — ''It is raining' and it is true', ''It might rain' and it is unknown', and ''It is sunny' and it is true' — are related concepts but do not correctly answer this specific question.": ""
